            <h2>Ethnic Clothing</h2>
            <h3>men's clothing--&emsp;</h3>
            <p>
                Yi men dress differently in different regions. Men in the "Zhe" dialect area wear star-chasing trousers that are wide
                and narrow at the bottom, men in the "Shengjia" dialect area wear medium-leg trousers, and men in the "Yinuo" dialect
                area wear large-leg trousers. Men wear a "headband" on their heads, which is a kind of hat made of cloth. The wrapping
                methods are different in different regions, but the shapes are similar. Men in some areas also wear silver earrings on
                their left ears. Men in almost all regions wear the Hero's Day, a traditional knife belt.
            </p>
            <h3>women's clothing--&emsp;</h3>
            <p>
                Young and middle-aged women all wear dark blue homespun cloth to wrap their heads, and their tops have short blue front
                lapels, the back lapels are longer than the front lapels, the round collars are inlaid with striped patterns of five
                colors, and the sleeves are bordered with three-color patterns;Young women wear green cloth headbands and silver necklaces with many silver bubbles. Their tops are in various colors
                of women's clothing. The round collar is inlaid with lace of different colors, and the waist is tied with blue patterns.
                When getting married, women will also wear "Zhalahuo" (chest ornament) and "Woga" (back ornament). The chest ornament is
                generally 1 meter long and is composed of 6 to 8 independent pieces of jewelry. It is usually made of about 10 pounds of
                sterling silver.
            </p>
            <h3>children's clothing--&emsp;</h3>
            <p>
                There are two main types of traditional children's hats worn by Yi babies: cockscomb hats and tiger-shaped hats. Some
                plant patterns are embroidered on the front of the cockscomb hat, symbolizing abundant food and clothing, health and
                longevity; the back of the hat is shaped like a chicken tail.Boys' traditional clothing is roughly the
                same as that of adults, with some having a piece of red cloth sewn on the trousers. Girls wear children's skirts with a
                straight top and pleated bottom.
            </p>
        </div>
